quran[7]{c,v,t,f}:
  50,1,"Qaf. By the glorious Qur'an."{1},footnotes:1:1
  50,2,"Nay; they wondered that a warner should have come to them from among themselves. The unbelievers said: “This indeed is a strange thing."{1},footnotes:1:1
  50,3,"What! When we are dead and reduced to mere dust, (shall we be raised to life)? Such a return is far-fetched.”"{1},footnotes:1:1
  50,4,"(Thus do they imagine, although) We know well what the earth takes away from them. With Us is a Record that preserves everything."{1},footnotes:1:1
  50,5,"They gave the lie to the Truth when it came to them. So they are now in a state of great perplexity."{1},footnotes:1:1
  50,6,"Did they never observe the sky above them: how We built it and beautified it; and it has no cracks;"{1}{2}{3},footnotes:1:1,footnotes:2:2,footnotes:3:3
  50,7,"and We have spread out the earth, and have set upon it firm mountains, and have caused it to bring out plants of all beauteous kinds?"{1},footnotes:1:1
  50,8,"All these are to serve as eye openers and as a lesson to every being who is prone to turn (to the Truth)."
  50,9,"We also sent down blessed water from the heaven, wherewith We caused gardens and harvest-grain to grow,"
  50,10,"and tall palm-trees with their thickly-clustered spathes;"